Gingerbread
  - Claire Margine

1 c ap flour
1 c pastry flour
1/2 c sugar
2 tsp cinnamon
2 tsp ground ginger
1/2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp salt
1 c molasses
1 egg
1/2 c melted butter
1/2 c half and half
1/4 c hot water

Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Lightly butter an eight-inch pan. Whisk together pastry flour and all-purpose flour. Stir in ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, and sugar until fully combined. Stir in melted butter, egg, half-and-half, molasses, and hot water. Bake for 40 min or until the gingerbread is springy to the touch.
